Option 3: The Naming
What it is: The user gives someone a name. Not a nickname—a true name. A word that describes what they are at their core. And once named, they cannot escape what that name means.

How it works: The order's oldest training is the ability to see someone's essential nature—not what they pretend to be, but what they are. When they speak that name aloud, it locks the person into that nature. A coward named cannot pretend bravery. A betrayer named cannot pretend loyalty. The named person can still act against their nature, but the effort destroys them over time.

The science hook: Rooted in linguistic philosophy—the idea that language doesn't describe reality, it creates it . The order has perfected this into a tool.

